{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770142970,"nonce":"6gsMdXLqee+UnsMoXv1SfvS3DgY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oBAOv","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/154","origin":"github"},"title":"Add Promptfoo framework for agent instruction testing","message":"## Problem\nBugs in agent instructions/documentation often recur even after fixes. We lack systematic regression testing for agent behavior, similar to how code is tested.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nImplement **Promptfoo** - an open-source, CLI-first framework for testing LLM agent instructions:\n\n### Why Promptfoo?\n- ✅ Open-source, Git-native workflow\n- ✅ YAML-based test configs (version controlled)\n- ✅ CI/CD integration for GitHub Actions\n- ✅ Red teaming/security testing support\n- ✅ Works with multiple agents (Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI, etc.)\n\n### Scope\n1. Install and configure Promptfoo\n2. Create initial regression test suite for known recurring bugs:\n   - Environment sourcing before builds\n   - Feature branch creation vs direct commits to main\n   - Git identity configuration\n   - Issue-first workflow adherence\n3. Add CI/CD integration\n4. Document testing workflow in `.agent/`\n\n### References\n- [Promptfoo GitHub](https://github.com/promptfoo/promptfoo)\n- Industry best practices: regression gates, behavior validation, version control for instructions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Promptfoo installed and configured\n- [ ] Test suite with 4+ regression tests\n- [ ] CI/CD integration (GitHub Actions)\n- [ ] Documentation in `.agent/testing/`\n- [ ] Tests pass on current instruction set\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null}]}